## Summary of Keyboard Shortcuts in Gentleman.Dots Repository

### Neovim Shortcuts
The main keybindings are defined in `/home/lr/ecoDev/documenting/nvim/Gentleman.Dots/GentlemanNvim/nvim/lua/config/keymaps.lua`:

#### Basic Shortcuts:
- `<C-b>` - Delete to the end of the word in insert mode without leaving insert mode
- `<C-c>` - Escape from other modes (insert, normal, visual)
- `<leader>uk` - Toggle Screenkey
- `<leader>bq` - Delete all buffers but the current one
- `<C-s>` - Save file with custom function
- `<leader>md` - Delete all marks

#### Tmux Navigation (with nvim-tmux-navigation plugin):
- `<C-h>` - Navigate to the left pane
- `<C-j>` - Navigate to the bottom pane
- `<C-k>` - Navigate to the top pane
- `<C-l>` - Navigate to the right pane
- `<C-\>` - Navigate to the last active pane
- `<C-Space>` - Navigate to the next pane

#### Obsidian Integration:
- `<leader>oc` - Check Obsidian checkbox
- `<leader>ot` - Insert Obsidian template
- `<leader>oo` - Open in Obsidian App
- `<leader>ob` - Show Obsidian backlinks
- `<leader>ol` - Show Obsidian links
- `<leader>on` - Create new note
- `<leader>os` - Search Obsidian
- `<leader>oq` - Quick switch

#### Oil (file manager):
- `-` - Open parent directory
- `<leader>E` - Open Oil in floating mode

#### Visual Mode Grep:
- `<leader>sg` - Grep selected text
- `<leader>sG` - Grep selected text (root directory)

### Additional Shortcuts from Other Plugin Files:

#### DAP (Debug Adapter Protocol):
- `<leader>d` - Debug group
- `<leader>dB` - Set breakpoint condition
- `<leader>db` - Toggle breakpoint
- `<leader>dc` - Continue
- `<leader>da` - Run with Args
- `<leader>dC` - Run to cursor
- `<leader>dg` - Go to line (no execute)
- `<leader>di` - Step into
- `<leader>dj` - Down
- `<leader>dk` - Up
- `<leader>dl` - Run last
- `<leader>do` - Step out
- `<leader>dO` - Step over
- `<leader>dp` - Pause
- `<leader>dr` - Toggle REPL
- `<leader>ds` - Session
- `<leader>dt` - Terminate
- `<leader>dw` - Widgets

#### Oil Keymaps:
- `g?` - Show help
- `<CR>` - Select
- `<C-s>` - Open in vertical split
- `<C-v>` - Open in horizontal split
- `<C-t>` - Open in new tab
- `<C-p>` - Preview
- `<C-c>` - Close
- `<C-r>` - Refresh
- `-` - Go to parent
- `_` - Open CWD
- `` ` `` - Change directory
- `~` - Change directory in tab
- `gs` - Change sort
- `gx` - Open external
- `g.` - Toggle hidden
- `g\` - Toggle trash

#### Copilot Chat Mappings:
- `<Tab>` (insert) - Complete
- `q` (normal) / `<C-c>` (insert) - Close
- `<C-l>` (both modes) - Reset
- `<CR>` (normal) / `<C-s>` (insert) - Submit prompt
- `grr` (normal) - Toggle sticky
- `grx` (normal) - Clear stickies
- `<C-y>` (both modes) - Accept diff
- `gj` (normal) - Jump to diff
- `gqa` (normal) - Quickfix answers
- `gqd` (normal) - Quickfix diffs
- `gy` (normal) - Yank diff
- `gd` (normal) - Show diff
- `gi` (normal) - Show info
- `gc` (normal) - Show context
- `gh` (normal) - Show help

### Tmux Shortcuts
Defined in `/home/lr/ecoDev/documenting/nvim/Gentleman.Dots/GentlemanTmux/tmux.conf`:

#### Basic Keymaps:
- `C-a` - Prefix key (instead of default `C-b`)
- `C-a C-a` - Send prefix
- `v` - Split window horizontally
- `d` - Split window vertically
- `K` - Kill all other sessions

### Zellij Shortcuts
Defined in `/home/lr/ecoDev/documenting/nvim/Gentleman.Dots/GentlemanZellij/zellij/config.kdl`:

#### Locked Mode:
- `Ctrl g` - Switch to normal mode

#### Pane Operations:
- `left` - Move focus left
- `down` - Move focus down
- `up` - Move focus up
- `right` - Move focus right
- `c` - Switch to rename pane mode
- `d` - New pane down + lock
- `e` - Toggle pane embed/floating + lock
- `f` - Toggle focus fullscreen + lock
- `h` - Move focus left
- `j` - Move focus down
- `k` - Move focus up
- `l` - Move focus right
- `n` - New pane + lock
- `p` - Switch to normal mode
- `r` - New pane right + lock
- `w` - Toggle floating panes + lock
- `x` - Close focus + lock
- `z` - Toggle pane frames + lock
- `tab` - Switch focus

#### Tab Operations:
- `1-9` - Go to tab 1-9 + lock
- `b` - Break pane + lock
- `n` - New tab + lock
- `r` - Switch to rename tab mode
- `s` - Toggle active sync tab + lock
- `t` - Switch to normal mode
- `x` - Close tab + lock
- `tab` - Toggle tab

#### Resize Operations:
- `+` / `=` - Increase size
- `-` - Decrease size
- `H-J-K-L` - Decrease in direction
- `h-j-k-l` - Increase in direction
- `r` - Switch to normal mode

#### Session Operations:
- `c` - Launch configuration plugin + lock
- `d` - Detach
- `o` - Switch to normal mode
- `p` - Launch plugin manager + lock
- `w` - Launch session manager + lock

#### Global Operations (Normal/Locked modes):
- `Alt + arrow keys` - Move focus/tab
- `Alt +` / `Alt =` - Increase size
- `Alt -` - Decrease size
- `Alt [` / `Alt ]` - Previous/Next swap layout
- `Alt f` - Toggle floating panes
- `Alt h-j-k-l` - Move focus/tab
- `Alt i` / `Alt o` - Move tab left/right
- `Alt n` - New pane

These are the comprehensive keyboard shortcuts configured in the Gentleman.Dots repository across Neovim, Tmux, and Zellij.
